<h2 id="useful-resources">Useful resources</h2>

<p>Sign up to the <a href="https://accessibility.blog.gov.uk/">GOV.UK accessibility blog</a>.</p>

<p>Join the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/communities/accessibility-community">GOV.UK accessibility community</a> and talk to other people across government with an interest in accessibility.</p>

<p><a href="https://gcs.civilservice.gov.uk/webinars/digital-accessibility-for-government-communicators/">Digital accessibility for government communicators</a> is a useful webinar run by the Government Communication Service (GCS).</p>

<p><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/perspective-videos/">Web accessibility perspectives by W3C</a> are a series of videos that show how accessible design helps people with disabilities.</p>

